what is it like having a baby generally speaking i e life changing aspects responsibilities it's the most rewarding thing to ever happen in life all the love they bring but it's also the most expensive time consuming job you will ever have and years without a vacation is a long time you don't have time to go out much and no extra money until you can get over the it's just too cute s he's gotta have it stage unless you have a great job lol you've got to get responsible keep formula diapers wipes extra food toys miniature furniture little clothes that stain all the time as well as a lot of doctor visits and sleepless nights at least the first year teething strange fevers rashes getting conked on the head by flying blocks trying to dodge flying food and still get the spoon in the hole wrestling a baby to get a diaper on when they've just learned how to roll over and crawl should be an olympic event but when you've been at work or the store and you come home and the arms fly in the air and you get a giggle and a grin and your heart melts laying on the couch snuggled together pretending to watch tv while baby sleeps and you watch baby sleep in your arms the triumph of the first tooth first crawling first walking stage each day is a day of little acheivements and it's an amazing journey of learning that will captivate your mind as well as your little ones good luck Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Characters in the Smurfs Infantilism The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Comanche Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Humphrey Bogart Friends Cliff Richard Shen Gong Wu The Amber Spyglass Futurama (TV series - season 5) Salad Fingers Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Diaper Jon Secada AFI 100 Years series Dog training Urinary incontinence Freddy Fender Care Bears Childbirth Joke The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Aerosmith The Sims Blankets (graphic novel) Demographics Kimberly-Clark Corporation Sea-Monkey Kodocha Shaggy dog story The Catch